“Given at Rome, on the third day before the Kalends of April, Constantine Augustus consul for the fourth time, and Gallicanus consul for the fourth time.''1

He took the next to the last day of March so that we might feel that this was done in the season of holy dayS, which, for the most part, come at that time.
